[normal]Written evidence submitted by the [bold]Palestine Solidarity Campaign [bold]Palestine Solidarity Campaign 
[normal]welcomes the opportunity to submit this evidence to the International Development Inquiry into DfID’s
[normal] work in the Middle East. Our submission covers DfID’s work in occupied Palestinian territory. 
[normal]The submission outlines 
[normal]the importance of Area C and East Jerusalem to the long term future of Palestinians, a Palestinian 
[normal]state and economic independence
[normal]. Give
[normal]n this, the submission suggests it is vital that DfID support the development of healthcare and educational facilities within Area C and East Jerusalem. Furthermore, it suggests this should be done in tandem with the FCO taking further action against Israe
[normal]l’s 
[normal]programme of 
[normal]illegal settlement 
[normal]building and demolitions of
[normal] Palestinian structures. 
[normal]In addition, the submission outlines that humanitarian aid in Gaza will 
[normal]fail to meet need 
[normal]until the blockade is lifted, and that significant infrastructural developmen
[normal]t will be required to prevent further 
[normal]humanitarian catastrophes. 
